    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for the discerning enthusiast is a pristine 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six. This naturally aspirated power plant utilizes six individual throttle bodies to deliver instantaneous response and a linear torque curve up to its 7,900 RPM redline. The Getrag 6-speed manual transmission provides tactile, precise engagement, paired with a perfectly calibrated limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance is complete: the dual-VANOS system has been overhauled, the rear subframe reinforced, and rod bearings replaced with VAC-coated shells. The chassis remains exceptionally taut with fresh OEM-spec bushings and Bilstein dampers, preserving the telepathic handling characteristics of the E46 platform. This is a mechanically flawless, turn-key example with zero deferred maintenance and a dry undercarriage.",
